This paper is about improving the performance of a deep learning model for image super-resolution, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also focuses on improving the speed of the model, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new CNN structure, which involves optimizing the mapping layer, suggesting that it may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image processing and restoration, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
